sentences.content: The following exercises allow me to fill in the prompts given the corresponding response lists in increasingly more difficult ordering until no response list is shown.
An erupting mountain is called a [_volcano_].
Australian animal with a pouch is a [_kangaroo_].
You bend your leg at the [_knee_].
You unlock a door with a [_key_].
You work a job to earn [_money_].
There are twelve months in a [_year_].
You get out of bed in the [_morning_].
A house has a [_roof_] on top.
To weigh yourself, you use a [_scale_].
You row a boat with two [_oars_].
You mail a letter in an [_envelop_].
Getting money back is called a [_refund_].
